{
  "stem": "9471.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "First of all, what was your husband-- tell us your husband's name.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What his name?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Julius Goldberger.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, Julius Goldberger, that was his name.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember, when we were married in city hall.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I had some friends.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were all witnesses.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we didn't have, even, a ring.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My girlfriend took the ring so I could have, you know, my wedding.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was Friday.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was raining.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they took us, then, for a-- for a lunch.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that was that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But we had a wonderful--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--time in Bari, because he had a very good job.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And like I said, I had a very good job.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And a year before we knew that-- oh, how we came to United States, because that's interesting too.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Before we came, you had to have affidavit, because they didn't let us go otherwise.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my husband find a telephone book, and he took all Goldbergers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He wrote about, I don't know, 100 letters.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't know how many letter, all over United States.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we got some replies, sorry, but they don't have any relatives in Europe, so they wish us luck, that's all.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But one family from Chicago, Alfred Goldberger, wrote us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was beautiful letter.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He says we are not related, because our grandparents already were born in United States.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But from this day, we consider you like us, relative.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we're going to be happy to help you to send you the papers and everything.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that was going on-- we were waiting over a year, till we finally could get it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They send us beautiful clothing and packages.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Every-- they were just wonderful.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The letters, the pictures, you know?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And when I was in Bari, I got pregnant.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
